	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98072451726279><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=98072451726279>RE: What in your opinion is the best Race for the Rogue?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=98072451726279#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 28th 11:31 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, I've actually played a few different races as a rogue and this is some of the info I've compiled (currently I've stuck with my barbarian btw)<br><br>Barbarians - Great Str for backstabs, it's so high you really don't have to put points in it if you don't want to.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'd suggest throwing some points into dex for proccing weapons later on, and agi is easy to raise with magic items.<br><br>Dark Elves - Their stats are kinda lacking in dex and str, but they're one of the more interesting races to roleplay, and again there are lots of items that'll raise attributes.<br><br>Dorfs - These lil guys pack a nice punch, they have good dex, but their agi is kinda low.  Now I'm not a big advocate of agi, because ROUGES SHOULD NOT SOLO! so if you toss some points into str and dex you'll whomp 'em hard and proc like mad.<br><br>Gnomes - They're short, they're underestimated (just like us rogues) and they have big noses.  Fairly balanced stats and tinkering can be fun.<br><br>Halflings - Too stereotypical!<br><br>Humans - Look like they were rejects from the GI Joe toy factory.<br><br>Wood Elves - Great agi, so you can focus all your points into str and dex, I'd reccomend putting most into str and the rest into dex, they also get hide and forage to start off with and faydwer is a great place for a newbie.<br><br>Half Elves - Have almost perfectly balanced stats for a rogue, they've got decent str, good agi and great dex.  Only problem is their chainmail hats look really goofy.<br><br>So to sum it all up in my experience Dex and Str are the most important stats to worry about.  Dex will help you proc weapons and hit with bows and Str will help you shank spines all that much harder.<br><br>Lyssara 15th level Rogue and climbing on Torvo<br>I've also got a 21st wood elf, and a 14th dorf rogue =)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
