	   <tr><td colspan=2>YOU CAN UNDO YOUR CAPS LOCK AT ANY TIME!!&nbsp;&nbsp;I have always been partial to wood elfs.  I am playing a ranger atm, but will be starting a rogue soon and it will prolly be another treehugger.  One thing to consider is that elves can wear med or sm armor, some of those other races get only sm, and I think barbs can only wear large (not sure on that).  You are restricted enough in your armor selection, might not want to make it any worse by playing a class that can only wear sm or large. I think the abilities have been covered enough, although don't waste points in dex for archery, as a ranger I can tell you it is nerfed, but dex does help with those procs, which you will want later in life.  Agi and Str should be your priorities, IMO, str does increase your atck rating, and agi makes you better defensively.  Like a ranger, rogues need all the defensive abilities and ac that they can get.  You are already going to kick that arse offensively, defense is where you will be weak, don't make it worse than it is. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
