	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 18th 7:52 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thats the million dollar question isn't it?&nbsp;&nbsp;People like to say that Barbarians and dorfs are, but it really depends on what you want your rogue to be.  I went for the best all around race in the game-a half elf.  They have best set of the "Rogue Trinity" str, dex, and agility.  I rank the races in which I think they will be as an overall rogue.  Not just str or agil or dex but all three.<br><br>1.  Half Elf--great mix of decent str, good dex and good dex.<br><br>2.  Halfling--str isn't great but boy are they quick and dexterous.<br><br>3.  Woold Elf--str is a little less than the half elf, but nice dex and agi<br><br>4.  Human--higher str than the half elf, but loses some agility and dexterity.<br><br>5.  Dwarf--excellent str and dex, but the agility is less than to be desired.<br><br>6.  Dark Elf--nice stats, but why pick a dark elf when you can get a race with comparable stats that can go into FP, Kelethin, Felwith, ect just to get  a mask that will allow you to go into ogguk, Grobb, Neriak later?<br><br>7.  Barbarian--str rocks! doh!  look at the dex and agi.  Good luck with pocketing those Sand Giants or dodging the attacks when you finds you messing around in his pockets.<br><br>8.  Gnome--last and least is the gnome.  Great dex and pretty nice agility but absolutely no strength.<br><br>That is how I rank the rogues.  If you want a damage machine, the list is going to change.  if you want a rich rogue that can pickpocket, the list is going to change.  If you want a rogue that just has a cool look, the list is going to change.  Rogues are a great class to play and we're not like those mana fools where a human wizard is inferior to a Erudite wizard (no offense to human wizards).  The rogue classes are the most versatile class in the game.  Even the gnomes make good rogues.  They are quick and nobody has hands like gnomes.  Bottom line, you can't make a bad decision when it comes to deciding what race to choose.  Just now that the different races of rogues take different strategies.  Well, didn't mean to make it a rogue manual or anything, hehe.<br>&nbsp;<br>Jest Acestalker<br>Assistant Guildmaster of Dark Hour on Solusek Ro</td></tr>
